Business Talk with Michael Avery has reached a new audience milestone, having passed 1.5 million views in February 2022. The online business talk show from BusinessTech has proved incredibly popular since its launch, and has started the new year strongly. Season 6 of Business Talk, presented by Monocle, went live at the end of January has featured excellent guests – including FNB CEO Jacques Celliers. This follows hugely successful earlier seasons, which were sponsored by Discovery Bank, EY, Discovery Business Insurance, EY-Parthenon, and Sage. Business Talk’s success in the market is thanks to its excellent host, impressive guest list, and high production quality. The show is hosted by highly-respected radio and TV personality Michael Avery. Avery is well known in business circles for his roles on Classic FM and Business Day TV – and as the anchor of the HOT Business show on HOT 1027. Avery is complemented by a stellar line-up of guests, which has included Dr Andrew Golding, chief executive of the Pam Golding Property group; Sim Tshabalala, joint chief executive of the Standard Bank Group; and Magda Wierzycka, co-founder of Sygnia. The show is then produced and edited by Broad Media Multimedia Manager Weich Malan and his team – who ensure the show is always up to a world-class standard. Business Talk is set for an excellent 2022, with plans for more seasons well underway. All Business Talk episodes can be watched on the following channels: Business Talk Website
